---
By: Edward Car/)enter
Locus:
  Page: 468
  Verse: 26
Tags:
  - Thoughts
---
Of all the hard facts of science. ...I know of none more solid and
fundamental than the fact that if you inhibit thought (and persevere), you
come at length to a region of consciousness below or behind thought. ...a
realization of an altogether vaster self than that to which we are
accustomed.
